Description: Fernandes Native X Electric Guitar Blue Sparkle Finish VG Condition Very good used condition Fernandes six-string electric guitar, circa 2005. Solid alder body in an unusual shape; bolt-on maple neck; 22-fret rosewood fingerboard; humbucker/Tele-style single-coil configuration. Made in China. The Native X offers lots of tonal choices coupled with excellent playing comfort for guitarists in many genres. Original black pickguard was replaced with a white pearl finish pickguard a few years back. All knobs (volume, tone), switch and pickups work. Strings have low action. I presume this has passive electronics since back panel is removable to access the interior wiring, and there’s no 9-volt battery slot. Guitar has a thick neck yet is very playable. The unusual "pattern" on the back of the neck is actually the wood itself, not discoloration, damage or a bad finish. Weight: 10 pounds. Body Length: 39 inches. Body Width at widest part: 13 inches. Body Thickness: 1.5 inches thick. Blue sparkle finish in excellent condition. No chips, dings, or scratches, just some slight wear from use. Needs a new set of strings. Will be shipped with a padded gig bag. Overall, a great starter guitar, or addition to your collection.
